cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the prevalence of graph processing across various application domains, which suggests that it could belong to sub-categories related to databases (cs.DB), social and information networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), software engineering (cs.SE), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study also focuses on the challenges faced by users when processing large graphs, which further supports the relevance of these sub-categories.
